 PostgreSQL's tag line claims that it's "The world's most advanced open source database." In  Part I of this series  we looked at storing the data - the model, structures, types and size limits - to give you a few reasons why PostgreSQL makes this claim. In Part II here, we'll look at data manipulation and retrieval, including indexing, virtual table features and query capabilities. For this series, we looked at what makes PostgreSQL stand out from other open source SQL databases, namely MySQL, MariaD